answers.body_markdown:
Add this to your code:

&lt;!-- language: lang-css --&gt;

    .parent &gt; div:first-child,
    .parent &gt; div:last-child {
      flex-shrink: 0;
    }

IE11, for whatever reason, needs `flex-shrink` disabled. (Probably because `min-height: auto` is the default setting on non-IE browsers, meaning that the items cannot shrink below the height of their content. But [in IE11 the default may be `min-height: 0`](https://stackoverflow.com/a/36247448/3597276). But then again, adding `min-height: auto` to IE11 doesn&#39;t solve the problem.)

